  "instructions": [
    "Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.",
    "Add the onion and garlic and cook until softened, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add the fennel seeds and thyme and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the barley, rice, quinoa, and bulgur and stir to coat with oil and mix with onion-garlic mixture.",
    "Add 4 cups of water and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 40-45 minutes, or until grains are tender and liquid has been absorbed.",
    "Fluff with a fork and season with salt and black pepper.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped parsley."
